					<head>Midrash</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Four fragments of midrashic commentaries.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="136v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Midrash rabah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מדרש רבה</title>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Midrash-Rabah_1985"/>
								</bibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Jellinek_1853" type="page">73-82</ref> of volume 2. </bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<note>
								<p>The text differs largely from the printed editions in many parts.</p>
								<p>The enumeration of chapters is irregular.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="marginal">
								<locus n="136r"/>A passage written in a geometrical design.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="137r" to="258v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sifra</title>
							<note>
								<p>The enumeration of diffirent divisions is not consistent.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Sifra_1999"/>
								</bibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Neusner_1988a"/>
								</bibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Neusner_1988b"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">בעזרת שוכן מעונים אתחיל תורת כוהנים. <locus n="137r"/>
							</incipit>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="259r" to="283v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sifre</title>
							<note>
								<p>The sections are not regularly marked throughout.</p>
								<p>Sifre on Numbers, folios <locus from="259r" to="315v"/>, on Deuteronomy, folios 316r-386v.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Sifre_1990"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="283v" to="386v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Peṭirat Aharon ve-Mosheh</title>
							<note>
								<p>Occasional marginal notes, partially cut away. </p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Jellinek_1853" type="page">91-95, 115-129</ref> of volume 1.</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex; Ashkenazi square script of approximately 12th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex</support>
								<extent>386 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>360</height>
										<width>265</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>270</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>386 folios (+2 vellum flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>48 quires of 8 leaves each (apart from no. 32 which has 10 leaves).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Margins slightly damaged at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="24 25" writtenLines="24 25">
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quire.</p>
									<p>Has some marginal notes, occasionally cut away.</p>
									<p>Pricking and hard-point ruling is visible.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script of approximately 12th century.</summary>
